com.seagullsw.appinterface.client

Class AppInterfaceConnectionFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.seagullsw.appinterface.client.AppInterfaceConnectionFactory

  • public class AppInterfaceConnectionFactory
extends java.lang.Object
    The "factory" class AppInterfaceConnectionFactory is non-instantiable, but provides static methods for the creation of AppInterfaceConnectionobjects representing client connections to the Application Interface Server using either socket- or HTTP-based communication protocols.
    See Also:
    SocketAppInterfaceConnection, HTTPAppInterfaceConnection

      • createDefaultConnection

        public static SocketAppInterfaceConnection createDefaultConnection()

        Returns a default socket-based connection to an Application Interface Server. This is the client of a socket at IP address "localhost" and port defined by the int constant com.seagullsw.appinterface.comm.AppInterfaceCommunicationConstants.DEFAULT_SOCKET_PORT (e.g. 1208).

        See Also:
        createDefaultSocketConnection()
